# AI Agent Package

## Architecture

The agent package is a **Python library** imported by the API. Routes are registered under `/agent`.

```
packages/agent/src/
├── schema.py           # Pydantic request/response models
├── settings.py         # AgentSettings configuration
├── core/
│   ├── agent.py        # get_agent() context manager
│   ├── manager.py      # Streaming + SSE formatting
│   ├── providers.py    # LLM provider factory
│   ├── prompt.py       # System prompt
│   └── storage.py      # Checkpoint saver
└── routes/
    ├── router.py       # create_agent_router()
    ├── health.py       # GET /agent/health
    ├── stream.py       # POST /agent/stream (SSE)
    ├── threads.py      # Thread management
    └── history.py      # Conversation history
```

## Key Patterns

- Library pattern: API imports agent, not standalone server
- Provider factory in `core/providers.py` (google/openai/anthropic/llamastack)
- Settings via `pydantic-settings` with `.env` support
- MCP tools loaded conditionally when `MCP_ENABLED=true`
- Checkpoint storage: in-memory (default) or PostgreSQL

## Commands

```bash
pnpm --filter @dagshub-ai-dev-plaform-support/agent test
pnpm --filter @dagshub-ai-dev-plaform-support/agent lint
```
